The European Union is changing the rules for obtaining visa
Individuals must go to service centers for visa applicants before their interview in the Consular Section, the waiting time cost will be reduced.
From 10 January 2011 the visa processing procedure at the Embassy and consulates of the United States will change.
With the new procedure, most applicants will have to go to service centers for Visa Applicants (AUC, by its initials in English) before their interview in the Consular Section.
ASC personnel will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for candidates, among which we mention the following:
The total cost to process the visa will be lower, it will no longer need to make a payment to get an appointment, another payment for visa processing and another for the courier delivers the document.
The aspirant will realize a single payment covering the three services.
The current rate will remain the same: the equivalent of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, $ 150 in the case of visa-application (here includes visas for temporary workers) and $ 390 for visa traders and investors.
Persons wishing to renew their visas will not have to attend an interview with the consular representative, they arise only at the ASC nearest where they will present documents and they will take their fingerprints.
Due to the fact that biometric information will be made in the CSA, applicants who want a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will stay less time.
Similarly, applicants for visas in the Consulates of Ciudad Juarez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo no longer pay the extra service costs $ 26.
For more information on the new procedure to apply for the visa, visit the following page http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
